==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Antivenin
<hw>An`ti*ve"nin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>antivenen</asp>, <asp>antivenine</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>anti-</ets> + L. <ets>venenum</ets> poison.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>The serum of blood rendered antitoxic to a venom by
repeated injections of small doses of the venom; also, the component of
such a serum which is antitoxic to the venom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antivivisection</ent>⟦br⟧
